issue_body:
### Which component is affected?

Qwik Runtime

### Describe the bug

When using `useSerializer$`, on the server it works as expected, but on the client/page side it does not deserialize the value (in this example it'll error it when clicking the +1s button)

```js
import { component$, useSerializer$ } from "@qwik.dev/core";
import { routeLoader$ } from "@qwik.dev/router";
import { Temporal } from "@js-temporal/polyfill";

export const useNow = routeLoader$(() => {
  return Temporal.Now.plainDateTimeISO().toString();
});

export default component$(() => {
  const now = useNow();
  const a = useSerializer$(() => ({
    initial: now,
    serialize(value) {
      return value.toString();
    },
    deserialize: Temporal.PlainDateTime.from,
  }));

  return (
    <>
      Current: {a.value.toString()}
      <button
        onClick$={() => {
          a.value = a.value.add({ seconds: 1 });
        }}
      >
        +1s
      </button>
    </>
  );
});
```

### Reproduction

https://stackblitz.com/edit/github-hkkawys3?file=src%2Froutes%2Findex.tsx

### Steps to reproduce

Click the "+1s" of the "broken" version, you'll get "now.value.add is not a function" error

btw, for some reason if you click on the "works" version first, the "broken" version will work too (make sure to click the reload button first)

### System Info

```shell
System:
    OS: Linux 6.18 Ubuntu Resolute Raccoon (development branch) 26.04 (Resolute Raccoon)
    CPU: (16) x64 AMD Ryzen 7 3700X 8-Core Processor
    Memory: 26.47 GB / 30.26 GB
    Container: Yes
    Shell: 5.3.3 - /bin/bash
  Binaries:
    Node: 25.2.0 - /home/wtct/.nvm/versions/node/v25.2.0/bin/node
    npm: 11.6.2 - /home/wtct/.nvm/versions/node/v25.2.0/bin/npm
  Browsers:
    Brave Browser: 144.1.86.148
    Chrome: 145.0.7632.45
    Firefox: 144.0.2
    Firefox Developer Edition: 144.0.2
  npmPackages:
    typescript: 5.9.3 => 5.9.3
    vite: 8.0.0 => 8.0.0
```

### Additional Information

https://discord.com/channels/842438759945601056/1483542875718291499

