issue_body:
### Describe the bug

Defining an event on a table makes opening this table impossible in designer.

### Steps to reproduce

-- Define a log table
DEFINE TABLE log TYPE NORMAL SCHEMAFULL PERMISSIONS NONE;
DEFINE FIELD created ON log TYPE datetime READONLY VALUE time::now() PERMISSIONS FULL;
DEFINE FIELD event ON log TYPE string PERMISSIONS FULL;
DEFINE FIELD table ON log TYPE string PERMISSIONS FULL;

-- Define a student table
DEFINE TABLE student TYPE NORMAL SCHEMAFULL PERMISSIONS NONE;
DEFINE FIELD created ON student TYPE datetime READONLY VALUE time::now() PERMISSIONS FULL;
DEFINE FIELD email ON student TYPE string PERMISSIONS FULL;
DEFINE FIELD first_name ON student TYPE string PERMISSIONS FULL;
DEFINE FIELD last_name ON student TYPE string PERMISSIONS FULL;

-- Define an event that should trigger creatig a log entry in the log table
DEFINE EVENT student_created ON student WHEN $event = 'CREATE' THEN (CREATE log SET `table` = 'student', event = $event);

After completing  these steps Surrealist won't allow you to open the student table in the designer with an error "Table must be a string". The screenshot below is shown what I see in Surrealist when I try to open the student table in the designer.

<img width="798" height="712" alt="Image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/38aaa455-be8c-45d1-9fbb-9797e4521264" />


### Expected behaviour

The table where the event defined must be accessable in the designer.

