issue_body:
## Problem

The test suite fails in shard 12 due to a broken assertion in `src/shared-components/ActionItems/ActionItemModal/ActionItemModal.spec.tsx` around line 1044.

**Test:** "should update preCompletionNotes field (covers line 705)"  
**File:** `src/shared-components/ActionItems/ActionItemModal/ActionItemModal.spec.tsx` (Lines 1027–1048)  
**Assertion that fails:** `expect(notesInput.value).toBe('T');`

## Root Cause

The test uses `user.keyboard('T')` which sends keystrokes to whatever element currently has focus. The Category Autocomplete frequently retains or reclaims focus when the modal opens, so the 'T' keystroke goes to the combobox instead of the preCompletionNotes input field. The click on the notes input isn't reliably focusing it, leaving `notesInput.value` as `''` and causing the assertion to fail.

## Proposed Fix

Replace the problematic keyboard call with targeted typing to ensure the keystroke goes to the correct input:

```typescript
// Current code (Lines ~1027-1048)
const notesInput = await screen.findByLabelText('preCompletionNotes');
await user.click(notesInput);
user.keyboard('T');
await waitFor(() => {
  expect(notesInput.value).toBe('T');
});

// Fixed code
const notesInput = await screen.findByLabelText('preCompletionNotes');
await user.click(notesInput);
// Ensure the input is actually focused before typing
await waitFor(() => expect(document.activeElement).toBe(notesInput));
// Use targeted typing instead of keyboard
await user.type(notesInput, 'T');
await waitFor(() => {
  expect(notesInput).toHaveValue('T');
});
```

## Additional Context

- Related PR: #7187
- Failing job: https://github.com/PalisadoesFoundation/talawa-admin/actions/runs/21879807101/job/63159369460?pr=7187
- This is a test-only fix; no component changes needed
- The fix ensures the test reliably types into the correct field

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] The test "should update preCompletionNotes field (covers line 705)" passes consistently
- [ ] Shard 12 completes successfully
- [ ] No other tests are broken by the change

