issue_body:
### Description

I am using a bar graph where the xaxis labels can be quite long. I would like to display the labels horizontally rather than at 45 degrees. When I do this (using `trim: true` and `rotate: 0`), the label is trimmed correctly, but the area where the text has been trimmed is blank (rather than showing the next category label).

### Steps to Reproduce

Create a bar graph with a long xaxis categor, set `trim` to `true` and rotate to 0:

```javascript
var options = {
  chart: {
    type: "bar",
  },
  series: [
    {
      name: "sales",
      data: [30, 40],
    },
  ],
  xaxis: {
    categories: [
      "this is a long label that keeps going and going and going and going and going",
      "test2",
    ],
    labels: {
      trim: true,
      rotate: 0,
    },
  },
};

var chart = new ApexCharts(document.querySelector("#chart"), options);

chart.render();
```
### Expected Behavior

Label should be trimmed and the label of the next category should be displayed.

### Actual Behavior

Label is trimmed, but the next category label is not displayed.

### Screenshots

First category label is trimmed correctly, but the "test2" label is not displayed:

![image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/ec8f38b7-b374-4721-9cea-ae54322ed1fa)

If I shorten the first category label, it displays correctly:

![image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/a8f9d8d3-ed69-4914-aea6-1246a934b875)

### Reproduction Link

https://codepen.io/downchapel/pen/ZEgWVqp

Thanks!

