### What theme are you using?

chakra-ui

### Version

6.2.5

### Current Behavior

If you have a schema with a selectable value, such as an enum, and you use the NativeSelectWidget then there is no placeholder

### Expected Behavior

There should be a placeholder

### Steps To Reproduce

Create a simple app, using the chakra-ui form


```tsx
import Form from "@rjsf/chakra-ui";
import validator from "@rjsf/validator-ajv8";


<Form
  schema={{
    type: "object",
    properties: {
      status: {
        type: "string",
        enum: ["pending", "approved", "rejected"],
      },
    },
  }}
  uiSchema={{
    status: {
      "ui:widget": "NativeSelectWidget",
    },
  }}
  validator={validator}
/>
```

This can be seen in the playground ([here](https://rjsf-team.github.io/react-jsonschema-form/#))

In the worst case you may not be able to select anything, this can be seen in the playground ([here](https://rjsf-team.github.io/react-jsonschema-form/#

