### Prerequisites

- [x] I have searched the existing issues
- [x] I understand that providing a [SSCCE](http://sscce.org/) example is tremendously useful to the maintainers.
- [x] I have read the [documentation](https://rjsf-team.github.io/react-jsonschema-form/docs)
- [ ] Ideally, I'm providing a [sample JSFiddle](https://jsfiddle.net), [Codesandbox.io](https://codesandbox.io) or preferably a [shared playground link](https://rjsf-team.github.io/react-jsonschema-form/) demonstrating the issue.

### What theme are you using?

mantine

### Version

6.4.2

### Current Behavior

Importing from @rjsf/mantine@6.4.2 fails in Next.js 16.1.6 with:
`Error [ERR_UNSUPPORTED_DIR_IMPORT]: Directory import '@rjsf/mantine/lib/Form' is not supported resolving ES modules imported from C:\...\node_modules\@rjsf\mantine\lib\index.js`
@rjsf/core@6.4.2 works fine with identical setup.

### Expected Behavior

@rjsf/mantine should import cleanly like @rjsf/core, without ESM directory import errors.

### Steps To Reproduce

1. Clone https://github.com/mantinedev/next-pages-template
2. yarn add @rjsf/mantine@6.4.2 @rjsf/core@6.4.2 @rjsf/utils@6.4.2 @rjsf/validator-ajv8@6.4.2
3. Edit pages/index.tsx:
```
import Form from '@rjsf/mantine'; // ❌ Fails
// import Form from '@rjsf/core';  // ✅ Works

export default function HomePage() {
  return <Form schema={{ type: 'object', properties: {
    name: { type: 'string', title: 'Name' },
  } }} />;
}
```
4. yarn dev → Build fails

### Environment

```markdown
- OS: Windows 11
- Node: v24.14.0
- yarn: 4.13.0

package.json deps:
{
  "@rjsf/core": "^6.4.2",
  "@rjsf/mantine": "^6.4.2", 
  "@rjsf/utils": "^6.4.2",
  "@rjsf/validator-ajv8": "^6.4.2",
  "next": "16.1.6",
  "react": "19.2.4"
}
```

### Anything else?

Root Cause (in node_modules/@rjsf/mantine/lib/index.js)
```
// ❌ BROKEN - directory imports (no .js extension)
import Form, { generateForm } from './Form';
import Templates, { generateTemplates } from './templates';
import Theme, { generateTheme } from './Theme';
import Widgets, { generateWidgets } from './widgets';
```

Compare @rjsf/core/lib/index.js:
```
// ✅ CORRECT - explicit file extensions
import Form, { generateForm } from './Form/index.js';
```

